Here are the MSTest approaches for each scenario:

**1. Windows-only (platform requirement)**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)] // custom, or use:
public void RegistryTest()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows");
    // ... registry code
}
```

**2. Skip in CI (environment-based)**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void GpuTest()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") == "true")
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU");
    // ...
}
```
Then filter in CI: `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"`

**3. Flaky external API (retry pattern)**
```csharp
// MSTest v3.x+ has built-in retry:
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)] // retries up to 3 times on failure
public void WeatherApiTest() { /* ... */ }
```

For older MSTest, use a manual loop or a custom attribute.

**4. Cleanup even on failure (use `[TestCleanup]` or `try/finally`)**
```csharp
[TestClass]
public class TempFileTests
{
    private string _tempFile;

    [TestInitialize]
    public void Setup()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    [TestCleanup] // runs even if the test fails
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void ProcessTempFile()
    {
        File.WriteAllText(_tempFile, "data");
        // ... assertions
    }
}
```

**Summary table:**

| Scenario | Approach |
|---|---|
| Platform-specific | `Assert.Inconclusive()` guard or condition attribute |
| Skip in CI | `[TestCategory]` + filter, or env-var guard |
| Flaky/retry | `[Retry(N)]` (MSTest v3+) |
| Cleanup on failure | `[TestCleanup]` — always runs post-test |

`Assert.Inconclusive()` marks the test as **skipped/warning** (not failed), which is the right signal for "can't run here" vs. "broken."
